<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - ENGINE FAN CONTROL - FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>An open or short to ground in the EFAN circuitry can be detected by the ECM during an 'On Demand" Engine
            Standard Test by the technician. IAT and ECT are monitored on a continuous basis. If a fault is detected, in
            either circuit, the EFAN control is disabled and the engine fan is on all the time.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="BOLD">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1901757">3.54</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the engine fan control circuit diagram and
            <emph type="BOLD">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1901758">3.15</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the voltage checks.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1901757" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1261" filename="../figeg1/EG1261.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.54 Engine Fan Control Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
        <table id="t19017100">
            <title>Table 3.15 Engine Fan Control Connector Checks</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="54p"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="54p"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="180p"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="S1T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Key on Engine Off - Voltage Checks at EFC Connector</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">(Check with EFC solenoid Disconnected, Ignition Key ON) Engine Off.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>+Test Points-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>A to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>0 v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>If voltage present, check for short to power</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>B to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Power should be available with key on, check fuse and/or circuit or open/shorts</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Circuit Resistance Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">(Check with EFC solenoid and battery positive cable disconnected,
                                    breakout box installed) &#38; ignition key off.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>+Test Points-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8 to B</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>If greater than 5 ohms, check for open circuit</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>F4 to A</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>If greater than 5 ohms, check for open circuit</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8 to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>> 100 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>If less than 100 ohms, check for short to ground</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>A to Grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>> 100 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>If less than 100 ohms, check for short to ground</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Operational Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">(Check with EFC solenoid connected and breakout box installed)</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">NOTE: This test should be done only when no ECT or IAT faults are
                                    present, voltages will change from 12v to 0v when fan is turned on by using the
                                    Output State Test.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>+Test Points-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8 to 19</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>0 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Solenoid energized - fan on</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8 to 19</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Solenoid de-energized - fan off</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>NOTE: Normal fan on temperature is 212&#176; (100&#176;C). Normal fan off temperature
                                is 207.5&#176; (97.5&#176;C)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Fault Code Descriptions</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>246 = The Engine Fan Control relay failed the output circuit check during a Key On
                                Engine Off Standard Test.
                            </para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">NOTE: For test purposes EFC solenoid can be turned On/Off through the
                                    Output State Test.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
